MALINOIS , a bit sluggish from the gate, saved ground into the lane but lacked a serious run. DATS DATS DATS , urged along while off the pace, retreated through the drive.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DELEGATED had his left hind shoe repaired in the paddock, edged up to a forward position early, saved ground stalking mid turn, eased out entering the lane, closed in between rivals leaving mid stretch, sustained under right handed asks, took over in deep stretch and prevailed. MARGIE'S FUN SON was steadied off heels near the five eighths, recovered and was pushed along to gain past the five sixteenths, angled six wide for the drive, gathered momentum past the three sixteenths, switched over to his corrected and lead and finished gamely to just miss. DOWSING ROD sped to the front, set a rated pace towards the inside, took some pressure around the turn, spurted clear two wide and under a drive in upper stretch, dug in when confronted nearing the sixteenth marker and gave way grudgingly. MONEY ROOM , five wide between foes near the half mile marker, advanced four wide to take aim approaching the stretch, ranged up in mid stretch then hung late. THE LAST JUMPSTART settled well back while saving ground, swung out to about the eight path in upper stretch, straightened away and closed steadily. PRINS FIRE , four then three wide between foes, stayed in touch while under asking into the lane, lacked a punch past mid stretch and weakened. INFINITE SERIES prompted the pace two to three wide outside the leader, failed to kick on soon into the lane, was checked sharply off heels leaving the three sixteenths and faded. SWEET SYNTAX was taken up soon after the break then swerved inward, regrouped to make a good run saving ground past the three eighths, eased out then back in for the drive and gave way. NOBLE RIVER hopped at the break, edged up six wide outside rivals nearing the half mile pole, dropped in a bit leaving the far turn, lacked a kick past the five sixteenths and faltered.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PARISH BELLE , quickly to the front, took to rating inside and turned away some early challenges entering the turn, spurted away and was nursed along past the five sixteenths, was guided out a couple paths soon into the lane, opened up under some right handed asks then maintained a comfortable advantage while confidently handled through the final seventy yards. NORTHERN GLOW steadied at the break, regrouped and was taken to rate, advanced well in hand while two wide past the five sixteenths, dropped in to take the rail route into the stretch, advanced inside foes, came back out and finished with good energy while second best. BRZINA , four deep nearing the half, was coaxed along four wide pursuing into the stretch, stayed on past mid stretch then faded a bit late. MAMA G'S WISH edged up three wide between runners nearing the half mile pole, was under heavy pressure pursuing to the inside of BRZINA nearing the lane, continued on past the eighth pole then faded. LA TRAVIESA settled in the clear early, angled in leaving the far turn, came back out to be four wide for the drive but lacked a rally. FRECCIA D'ARGENTO , unprepared as the gates sprung, was off three to four lengths slow, raced well back leaving the far turn, came out some in the drive and had belated action under steady hand encouragement. BETCHA BY GOLLY was sent up two wide between rivals to briefly challenge with a half mile remaining, dropped in when failing to keep pace with the winner past the three eighths, remained in range to upper stretch then gave way. There was a stewards inquiry into the start of FRECCIA D'ARGENTO. No action was deemed necessary.
